member.name: Amy Zhang
member.bio: Amy X. Zhang is an associate professor at University of Washington's Allen School of Computer Science and Engineering, where she directs the Social Futures Lab. Her research interests are in social computing and HCI.

member.name: Vinay Koshy
member.bio: Vinay Koshy is a postdoc at the University of Washington. He is interested in using AI to facilitate collective decision-making processes, particularly in the context of online community governance.

member.name: Ruotong Wang
member.bio: Ruotong Wang is a Ph.D. student at University of Washington CSE. She is interested in understanding and developing sociotechnical systems that facilitate communication and collaboration among diverse community members.

member.name: Galen Weld
member.bio: Galen Weld is a PhD student whose work focuses primarily on large-scale analyses of social media platforms' governance and content moderation strategies, with a particular focus on reddit.

member.name: Kevin Feng
member.bio: Kevin is a PhD student in Human Centered Design & Engineering at the University of Washington. His is interested in systems and tools that foster collaboration between diverse stakeholders, particularly within UX design and machine learning workflows.

member.name: Leijie Wang
member.bio: Leijie Wang is a PhD student of Computer Science at the University of Washington. He's interested in content moderation systems that respect people's expectations about privacy and fairness on various online platforms.

member.name: Alicia Guo
member.bio: Alicia is a PhD student at the University of Washington CSE. Her research interests are in creativity support tools and representations of generated content in human-AI systems.

member.name: Teanna Barrett
member.bio: Teanna (she/her) is a PhD at the University of Washington CSE. She is interested in building data scientists' capacity to reason ethically through their work and challenge Western-centric data ethics paradigms through Black thought.

member.name: Matthew Bilik
member.bio: Matthew is a PhD student in Human Centered Design & Engineering at the University of Washington. He is interested in machine representations of expertise and designing and assessing socio-technical systems in high-stakes decision-making contexts.

member.name: Andre Ye
member.bio: Andre Ye is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and philosophy. His primary research interest is in building more robust and responsible machine & deep learning systems.

member.name: Shreya Sathyanarayanan
member.bio: Shreya Sathyanarayanan is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying Computer Science. Her research interests are in HCI, designing and developing tools for online collaboration, and addressing misinformation.

member.name: Bingcan(Gloria) Guo
member.bio: Bingcan(Gloria) Guo is an exchange student at the University of Washington. She is an undergraduate student at The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology studying Data Science and Computer Science. Her research interests are gamification and understanding online communities.

member.name: Andrew Shaw
member.bio: Andrew Shaw (he/him) is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and philosophy. His resesarch interests are in computer and AI ethics, particularly regarding the impacts of sociotechnical systems on marginalized communities.

member.name: Lin Qiu
member.bio: Lin Qiu is a BS/MS student at the University of Washington in Computer Science. Her research interests are in HCI and Social Computing.

member.name: Sam Wong
member.bio: Sam is a masters student at the University of Washington in Technology Innovation. His research interests are in human computer interaction and social computing, specifically in building systems that facilitates understanding and participation in an online social setting.

member.name: Aadit Barua
member.bio: Aadit Barua is an undergraduate student at The University of Texas at Austin studying Computer Science and Math. His current research interests are in human-AI interaction, particularly creativity support tools and social computing.

member.name: Tony Zhou
member.bio: Tony is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science. He's broadly interested in HCI and science communication, currently focusing on understanding decentralized social media and end-user personalized feed curation.

member.name: Nick Vincent
member.bio: Nick is a Postdoctoral Scholar working with the Social Futures Lab at UW and the Computational Communication Lab at UC Davis. His research aims to give the public more voice in determing how the AI systems we all contribute data to are used.

member.name: Quan Ze (Jim) Chen
member.bio: Quan Ze (Jim) is a former PhD student, now postdoc in SFL. He is interested in understading disagreement and ambiguity in human annotation and building  crowdsourcing and human-in-the loop workflows.

member.name: Xinyi Zhou
member.bio: Xinyi Zhou is a Postdoctoral Scholar at the University of Washington. Her research interests are broadly in the intersection of data mining, machine learning, natural language processing, and social computing and their applications to combat m/disinformation.

member.name: Jina Yoon
member.bio: Jina Yoon is a PhD student of Computer Science at the University of Washington. Her current research interests are in fostering empathetic conversation, combating misinformation, and leveraging addictive design for good. She also really likes to play video games.

member.name: Inyoung Cheong
member.bio: Inyoung Cheong is a PhD student of Law at the University of Washington. Her research explores AI policy, governance, and regulatory approaches to mitigate foreseeable societal harms and developing interventions that promote accountability.

member.name: Simona Liao
member.bio: Simona Liao (she/they) is an undergraduate student at the University of Washington studying computer science and GWSS (Gender, Women, and Sexuality Studies). She is interested in Virtual Reality platforms and communities, and how to design them against harassments.

member.name: Tony Li

member.name: Anson Huang

member.name: Kathryn Yurechko
